Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
detachSdpGroup(25.10)                                    detachSdpGroup(25.10)

Name
       detachSdpGroup  - Detaches the specified Structured Data Path (SDP) ob-
       ject from the parent group

Syntax
       detachSdpGroup

       [-help]

       -name {<objNames>}

       Detaches the specified Structured Data Path (SDP) object from the  par-
       ent group.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation for each detachSdpGroup parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man detachSdpGroup

       -name {<objNames>}
              Specifies  the  name  of  the SDP object to be detached from the
              parent group.

